DENGUE/DHF - FRANCE (ST. MARTIN): CONFIRMED
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Thu, 19 Jan 2006 23:36:50 -0500 (EST)
From: <Sylvie.CASSADOU@sante.gouv.fr>

I am an epidemiologist working in the Antilles-Guyane Regional
Epidemiologic Unit of the French National Institute for Public Health
Surveillance. I am writing in response to your request for information
about dengue in St Martin:
In effect, a dengue outbreak occurred in 2005 in Guadeloupe (St Martin
belongs to Guadeloupe). It started in July [2005] and reached its maximum
in September. Now [Jan 2006] it is [tapering off].
For the [French] part of St Martin, the number of people who consulted a
general practitioner for suspicion of dengue between July and December
[2005] was estimated to be 335 cases. For the first week in January 2006, 7
confirmed cases (serology) have already been recorded. So the outbreak is
not yet completely finished in St Martin.
You can find more information about the actual dengue outbreaks in
Martinique and Guadeloupe on the following websites:
<http://www.invs.sante.fr>
<http://www.martinique.sante.gouv.fr> (BASAG publication)
--
Dr Sylvie Cassadou
CIRE Antilles Guyane
Direction de la Sante et du Developpement Social de Guadeloupe
Rue des archives Bisdary
97113 Gourbeyre
